+### `getStatus(): Promise<AnimatorStatusDoc>`
+
+Return the current rate-limit / back-off status. Returns a default running state document if no back-off has been recorded. Use this to check whether the Animator is paused before dispatching work.
+
+```typescript
+const status = await animator.getStatus();
+if (status.state === 'paused') {
+  console.log('Paused until', status.pausedUntil);
+  console.log('Back-off level', status.backoffLevel);
+}
+```
+
+See § Rate-Limit Back-Off for the full back-off configuration and escalation table.
